{"analytics_identifier":"OT1409","base_path":"/government/organisations/national-space-operations-centre","content_id":"6b681c1a-a04b-40fa-bddd-d331c2f730e2","description":"We develop and operate the UK’s space surveillance and protection capabilities. NSpOC is part of the Ministry of Defence , the UK Space Agency , and the Met Office .","details":{"acronym":"NSpOC","alternative_format_contact_email":"correspondence@ukspaceagency.gov.uk","body":"<div class=\"govspeak\"><p>We develop and operate the UK’s space surveillance and protection capabilities.</p>\n\n<p><abbr title=\"National Space Operations Centre\">NSpOC</abbr> is part of the <a class=\"brand__color\" href=\"/government/organisations/ministry-of-defence\">Ministry of Defence</a>, the <a class=\"brand__color\" href=\"/government/organisations/uk-space-agency\">UK Space Agency</a>, and the <a class=\"brand__color\" href=\"/government/organisations/met-office\">Met Office</a>.</p>\n</div>","brand":"foreign-commonwealth-development-office","foi_exempt":false,"logo":{"crest":"single-identity","formatted_title":"National Space<br/>Operations Centre"},"ordered_corporate_information_pages":[{"href":"/government/organisations/national-space-operations-centre/about/procurement","title":"Procurement at NSpOC"}],"ordered_featured_documents":[{"document_type":"Blog post","href":"https://space.blog.gov.uk/2026/05/05/the-king-visits-site-of-new-uk-space-agency-project-to-safeguard-satellites-in-an-increasingly-crowded-space/","image":{"alt_text":"The King unveiling the plaque for Project NOVA in Bermuda. Credit: Government of Bermuda.","high_resolution_url":"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/media/6a01c74d4fb0713aa63ea708/s712_16554_EV_Kings-Royal-Visit-UK-Space-Agency_046-2048x1366__2_.jpg","medium_resolution_url":"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/media/6a01c74d4fb0713aa63ea709/s465_16554_EV_Kings-Royal-Visit-UK-Space-Agency_046-2048x1366__2_.jpg","url":"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/media/6a01c74d4fb0713aa63ea707/16554_EV_Kings-Royal-Visit-UK-Space-Agency_046-2048x1366__2_.jpg"},"public_updated_at":"2026-05-05T00:00:00.000+01:00","summary":"<div class=\"govspeak\"><p>During The King’s visit to Bermuda, His Majesty visited the site which will be the first of the UK’s new global network of optical telescopes designed to protect the satellites that millions of people depend on every day.</p>\n</div>","title":"The King visits site of new UK Space Agency project to safeguard satellites in an increasingly crowded space "},{"document_type":"Blog post","href":"https://space.blog.gov.uk/2026/02/18/first-impressions-of-working-in-nspoc/","image":{"alt_text":"James Carmichael, NSpOC Deputy Head (Civil Operations).","high_resolution_url":"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/media/6996e42d047739fe61889dfc/s712_Adobe_Express_-_file__2_.jpg","medium_resolution_url":"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/media/6996e42db33a4db7ff889dfe/s465_Adobe_Express_-_file__2_.jpg","url":"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/media/6996e42dbfdab2546272bfb3/Adobe_Express_-_file__2_.jpg"},"public_updated_at":"2026-02-18T00:00:00.000+00:00","summary":"<div class=\"govspeak\"><p>Today we talk to James Carmichael, Deputy Head (Civil Operations) who recently joined NSpOC and has responsibility for civil operations.</p>\n</div>","title":"First impressions of working in NSpOC"},{"document_type":"Blog post","href":"https://space.blog.gov.uk/2025/07/11/uk-space-safety-centre-marks-one-year-milestone/","image":{"alt_text":"","high_resolution_url":"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/media/6871026c81dd8f70f5de3e9c/s712_chilbolton_gov_uk.jpg","medium_resolution_url":"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/media/6871026c2cfe301b5fb67ab6/s465_chilbolton_gov_uk.jpg","url":"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/media/6871026c10d550c668de3e9c/chilbolton_gov_uk.jpg"},"public_updated_at":"2025-07-11T00:00:00.000+01:00","summary":"<div class=\"govspeak\"><p>Millions across the UK ar